posts.author: KilroyJCNJ
posts.title: Astute Observation

twitter.content: Im curious,  why dont i see one Trump voter complaining about losing their food stamps?

posts.raw_content:
Usually, the biggest factor in price of consumer goods is energy costs. When gas/diesel prices went through the roof, it spiked the price of every consumer good because they have to get from the manufacturer/producer to the consumer.

I have really been baffled by why, with gas/diesel prices at historic lows, there has not been a corresponding reduction in the cost of consumer goods, particularly fast food and groceries.

Seeing that chart of how SNAP went from $80 billion a year to nearly $160 billion a year has suddenly made it all clear. Just like how federally guaranteed loans caused tuition to skyrocket, federally guaranteed food funds have caused food prices to skyrocket.

The marketplace can’t adjust that quickly. They used COVID as an excuse to basically dump billions of dollars into the food purchasing side of the equation without putting any money into the food production side.

Consequently, with the supply of food staying roughly the same but demand doubling, food prices shot up. It’s also clear why fast food is now nearly unaffordable because EBT became a way to subsidize fast food purchases that the government paid for.

Marjorie Taylor Greene criticized Trump recently for not bringing grocery prices down enough. Somebody needs to explain to her that Trump is doing his part with trade and energy prices, but it’s the entire SNAP apparatus specifically that is ruining grocery prices for Americans.

Likewise, somebody on Trump‘s team needs to alert him to this issue and show how basically SNAP needs to be completely overhauled. I like the suggestion where all you can buy with it are raw staples for survival. Things like eggs, milk, bread, cheese, and vegetables. No brand names, no junk food, no fast food, especially no luxuries like candy and soda. And make SNAP cards into phone apps tied to biometrics like fingerprint or face scan to prevent reselling food stamps for cash to buy drugs.

Yes, of course getting rid of the illegal immigrants will also help, but we’ve seen the charts that show the ethnicities where the food stamps are going, and they’re clearly not going to legacy Americans down on their luck. So I think right now this food stamp/EBT issue needs a lot more attention from the America First/MAGA crowd.
